Event.EventDescription:
Come celebrate the 89th Birthday Commemoration of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. in the Fourth Street Lobby of the Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. Library
150 East San Fernando Street, San jose
The celebration will include:
Multi-cultural drumming;
Dr. Clayborne Carson, Director of the Martin Luther King, Jr., Research and Education Institute;
Prof. Scott Meyers- Lipton on the legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. for today;
Members of the Community will read excerpts from several of Dr. King's most momentous speeches;
Reflection on Dr. B.R. Ambedkar, the MLK of India;
Dance of Peace.
This event is free and open to the public and is wheelchair accessible.
Seating is limited.

We will be watching Bella, a love story that goes beyond romance.
Free snacks and drinks.
Closed captions provided for deaf and hard of hearing students.&nbsp;

William M. Tsutsui, &ldquo;The King of Monsters: Godzilla and Postwar Japan&rdquo;
<br />
<br />
Since Godzilla&rsquo;s first appearance over sixty years ago, the King of the Monsters has become a cinematic icon and a globally recognized symbol of Japan.  But what can a giant, fire-breathing movie monster tell us about Japanese culture and Japan&rsquo;s national experience since World War II?  This talk will explore the serious lessons to be learned from the thirty Godzilla films and the growing worldwide popularity of the King of the Monsters, especially in the wake of the 2011 Fukushima nuclear disaster. <br />
<br />
Event is free and open to the public.&nbsp;
